CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1784569707
OL,3,CJo Stevens no longer Welsh Secretary
OL,4,Cas Andy Burnham becomes PM
OL,6,FThe First Minister of Wales, Rhun ap
OL,7,FIorwerth, has congratulated Andy
OL,8,FBurnham on his appointment as Prime
OL,9,FMinister, saying the switch presents
OL,10,Fan opportunity to redefine the
OL,11,Frelationship between the Welsh and UK
OL,12,FGovernments.
OL,14,FHe said: "I know that Andy Burnham
OL,15,Fshares my belief in the power of
OL,16,Fdevolution to improve the lives of the
OL,17,Fpeople we serve.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/7
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,432,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1784569707
OL,3,CJo Stevens no longer Welsh Secretary
OL,4,Cas Andy Burnham becomes PM
OL,6,F"In that spirit, I hope we can speak
OL,7,Fthe same language when it comes to
OL,8,Fdevolving powers out of Westminster by
OL,9,Fstrengthening, not bypassing, Wales's
OL,10,Fnational parliament and its ability to
OL,11,Fempower people and communities.
OL,13,F"I look forward to an early meeting
OL,14,Fwith the new Prime Minister to agree
OL,15,Fhow we can give Wales the powers it
OL,16,Fneeds to grow the economy and build a
OL,17,Ffairer, more prosperous future for
OL,18,Fall."
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/7
